'''Gray Rot''' was a plague that caused the skin of the infected being to turn gray and decay. The skin then became scabrous and gray until it eventually cracked and ulcerated. [[Death/Legends|Death]] would then follow a few painful [[Standard day/Legends|days]] later. It was treatable only within the first few days of infection, in its early stages, with [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]].

Some [[Womp rat/Legends|womp rats]] on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] carried this plague and could inoculate it by biting their prey. In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], [[Melios Purl]] tasked a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] to help him investigate a potential outbreak, and deliver a much needed vaccine to the [[Moisture farmer/Legends|moisture farmers]] across Tatooine.<ref name="AED">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Gray Rot is mentioned in [[Star Wars Galaxies|''Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided'']] by [[Tekil Barje]], who asks players to help him and take a vaccine to his infected friend [[Dagonel Dimms|Dagonel "Digger" Dimms]]. In the same game, Melios Purl seeks assistance in [[Bestine (city)/Legends|Bestine]] to perform analysis on an infected womp rat, and find a vaccine for the terrible plague.

